<h2>About</h2>
<p>Source code for the MQM Scorecard is available from <a href="https://github.com/multidimensionalquality/qt21-scorecard/" target="_blank">https://github.com/multidimensionalquality/qt21-scorecard/</a>. The MQM Scorecard is an implementation of the <a href="http://qt21.eu/mqm-definition">Multidimensional Quality Metrics (MQM) framework</a> for quality assessment. It provides an easy-to-use interface to conduct segment-based review of translated documents.</p>
<h3>The development team</h3>
<p>The MQM Scorecard has been developed in a collaboration between the German Research Center for Artificial Intelligence (DFKI) GMbH, the Brigham Young University Translation Research Group (BYU TRG), and LTAC Global.</p>
